tinguished graduate of virginia military institutes air force rotc program in  he has commanded a fighter squadron two fighter wings a numbered air force and us air forces in europe and allied air forces central europe prior to becoming chief of staff of the air force the general served as commander of air combat command at langley air force base jumper has also served at the pentagon as deputy chief of staff for air and space operations as the senior military assistant to two secretaries of defense and as special assistant to the chief of staff for roles and missions a command pilot with more than  flying hours principally in fighter aircraft jumper served two tours in southeast asia accumulating more than  combat hours jumper retired from the air force on november   in june  jumper joined board of directors of science applications international corporation a federal contractor company on march   jumper become saics ceo and was essential in splitting the company into two after the split jumper remained the ceo of the company which changed its name to leidos jumper retired as ceo in july  when roger krone succeeded him as the companys new ceo but jumper stayed on as chairman of the companys board of directors educationedit  hampton high school hampton virginia  bachelor of science degree in electrical engineering virginia military institute lexington  squadron officer school maxwell afb alabama  air command and staff college maxwell afb alabama  master of business administration degree golden gate university san francisco california  national war college fort lesley j mcnair washington dc assignmentsedit june  – july  student pilot th pilot training squadron moody air force base georgia july  – september  c upgrade training sewart afb tennessee october  – october  c pilot th tactical airlift squadron phu cat air base south vietnam november  – july  f upgrade training st tactical fighter squadron george afb california july  – may  instructor pilot weapons officer and